---
/**
 * Example page showcasing the AuthorBio component
 * This demonstrates how the component appears in context
 */

import DefaultLayout from '@layouts/DefaultLayout.astro';
import AuthorBio from '@components/education/AuthorBio.astro';

const pageTitle = "Author Bio Component Example";
const pageDescription = "Example showcasing the AuthorBio component implementation";

// Example author data (matching your content structure)
const authorData = {
  name: "James Carter",
  title: "Senior Casino Game Analyst", 
  credentials: [
    "15+ years casino industry experience",
    "Certified Gaming Professional", 
    "Mathematics degree with focus on probability theory"
  ],
  bio: "James has dedicated his career to analyzing casino games and helping players understand the mathematics behind gaming. His expertise spans across all major casino games with a particular focus on roulette variants and probability theory."
};
---

<DefaultLayout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription}>
  <main class="container">
    <article class="content-article">
      <header class="article-header">
        <h1>Complete Roulette Rules Guide</h1>
        <p class="article-lead">Master roulette with our comprehensive rules guide covering betting options, payouts, and gameplay for European, American, and French variants.</p>
      </header>
      
      <div class="article-content">
        <h2>Understanding the Basics</h2>
        <p>Roulette is one of the most iconic casino games, combining elements of chance with strategic betting. The game revolves around a spinning wheel with numbered pockets and a betting layout where players can place various types of wagers.</p>
        
        <h3>The Roulette Wheel</h3>
        <p>The standard European roulette wheel contains 37 pockets numbered 0 through 36. The American version includes an additional 00 pocket, bringing the total to 38. This seemingly small difference has a significant impact on the house edge and your winning probabilities.</p>
        
        <h3>Betting Options</h3>
        <p>Roulette offers a wide variety of betting options, from simple color bets to complex corner and street wagers. Understanding these options and their corresponding payouts is essential for developing an effective playing strategy.</p>
        
        <p>The key to enjoying roulette is understanding that it's a game of pure chance. While betting systems and strategies can make the game more engaging, no system can overcome the built-in house edge.</p>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Author Bio Component -->
      <AuthorBio 
        name={authorData.name}
        title={authorData.title}
        credentials={authorData.credentials}
        bio={authorData.bio}
      />
    </article>
  </main>
</DefaultLayout>

<style>
  .container {
    max-width: var(--grid-max-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--space-m) var(--grid-gutter);
  }
  
  .content-article {
    max-width: 70ch;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  
  .article-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
    text-align: center;
  }
  
  .article-header h1 {
    font-size: var(--font-size-4);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--foreground-color);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-m);
    line-height: 1.1;
  }
  
  .article-lead {
    font-size: var(--font-size-1);
    color: var(--color-neutral-700);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }
  
  .article-content {
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--foreground-color);
  }
  
  .article-content h2 {
    font-size: var(--font-size-2);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--foreground-color);
    margin: var(--space-xl) 0 var(--space-m) 0;
  }
  
  .article-content h3 {
    font-size: var(--font-size-1);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--foreground-color);
    margin: var(--space-l) 0 var(--space-s) 0;
  }
  
  .article-content p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-m);
  }
  
  /* Mobile adjustments */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .container {
      padding: var(--space-s) var(--space-s);
    }
    
    .article-header h1 {
      font-size: var(--font-size-3);
    }
    
    .article-lead {
      font-size: var(--font-size-0);
    }
  }
</style>